The file here is a bluray rip, but encoded as an MKV file. As a fellow Macbook Pro user, I recommend VLC player for playback (though I'd recommend VLC for just about any video playback). 

If you want to convert it to a format that can be used for the PS3 or other devices, use MKVTools, which has presets for the PS3, XBox, iPad, etc. Before actually converting the file, it'll try extracting the audio and video (separately) and placing them in a different container. So if the video is already in the right format for PS3 playback for example but the audio isn't, it'll extract the video, then convert the audio, then put them in an MP4 container. The whole process takes less than half an hour if the video doesn't need converting.
